** Dinobot didn't think that this was funny at all, hearing Tavatron's few 
chuckles as he was sure that she had caught sight of his problem.
It wasn't his fault that this...this...THING had come plummeting from the 
sky only to render his snout numb for the few first moments of shock before 
clinging to it and resisting to remove itself.
He finally stops shaking his head and glared at the black piece of fur which 
had pirched itself on the flat of his snout, frowning and glaring at it as 
he stood completely still.
Dinobot glanced over towards Tavatron as he heard her yell out something but 
detecting no beings about other then himself that she could possibly be 
speaking to. However, with this passenger on his nose, he paid her vocal 
words no mind.
This had to be, not the most uncomfortable situation but the most strange 
and unexpected he had ever lived through. Shaking his head momentarily to 
see if it had loosened its hold enough to be moved off. But it seemed to be 
no use and he snarled in frustration.
Of all the things, which must occur, something that he would never recall 
for fear of losing face and dishonor himself by it's telling.
Dinobot continued to glare at the black ball before lowing his head enough 
so that his transmetal claws might get a chance to grab a hold of it and 
remove it, with or without injury. He still didn't know if it was alive or 
not. But it was coming off either way as far as his concerns went.
He snarled as he heard Tavatron's voice become closer to him, snapping his 
head up towards her and growling deeply with growing aggression. He was 
embarrassed by this situation and a known way to cover that up was an 
attitude. This was foolish and of all the transformers in the world it had 
to occur to him?!
Dinobot shifted and snarled, his tail thrashing slightly behind him as he 
glared at Tavatron, it obvious from his expression that if she laughed she 
just might get a nice swipe up side the head. To him this was NOT funny in 
the slightest and the fast this fur ball was removed the sooner he could 
ground it into the dust and regain his posture.**
